<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ADJUST/INSTALL - PINION BEARING PRELOAD ADJUSTMENT
        (TRIAL BUILD-UP TEST)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1401603" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="4">
        <title>PINION BEARING PRELOAD ADJUSTMENT (TRIAL BUILD-UP TEST)</title>
        <para>The pinion bearing spacer thickness controls bearing preload. The spacer size for correct preload can be
            predetermined by using a "Trial Build-Up" procedure as follows:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble pinion bearing cage, cups and bearing spacer (without pinion or oil seal) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401634">Figure 34</hotlnk>). Use nominal size spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401635">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401634" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401634" filename="../figg14/G1401634.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Trial Build-Up Parts</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1401635" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401635" filename="../figg14/G1401635.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Nominal Pinion Bearing Spacer Thickness</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>During the assembly procedure, center bearing spacer between the two bearing cones.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate bearings and place the assembly in a press. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the
                CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes. Position sleeve or spacer so that load is applied
                directly to the backface of the outer bearing cone (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401636">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401636" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401636" filename="../figg14/G1401636.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Measuring Bearing Preload</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply press load to the assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401636">Figure 36</hotlnk>). Wrap soft wire or strong string around the bearing cage,
                attach spring scale and pull steadily. Preload is correct when torque required to rotate the pinion
                bearing cage is from 10 to 20 in-lbs. (1.1 to 2.3 N&#8226;m). This specification is translated into
                spring scale readings in
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl1401604">Table 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
